=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: New Recruits</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The idea of killing an npc selected by the leader sounds good, but will be difficult to get the timing right.  We would have to wait for an npc to come into the area that was just the right level.  Seems like a lot of trouble to go through. <BR>  <BR> We should go with the idea of a guild member giving a recommendation for a recruit, then the rest of us post if we accept or not.  We could say we need 5 positive posts or something like that.  this would save time and make sure that everyone approves of the recruit.</font><P>Leader of the Shanks, until I get killed or you find somebody better...<P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE>